title: Jennifer Lopez's "Cherry-Mocha" Nails Prove the Trend Is Here to Stay
description: Since the year started, celebrities haven't been holding back with the beauty inspiration, from pixie cuts at the 2024 Golden Globes to Zendaya's swoon-worthy "strawberry milk" nails that accompanied her engagement. The latest celeb to join the party? None other than Jennifer Lopez. The singer recently traded her awards-show-ready nude manicure for a fresh set of "cherry-mocha"" nails that have us simply drooling. Lopez's latest manicure comes just as the color combo has found its way to the top of our FYPs (again), just a few months after making its viral debut last fall. Although other stars like Kate Moss and Kylie Jenner have embraced the trend, Lopez's interpretation is our favorite to date thanks to celebrity manicurist Tom Bachik. But it's far from the pair's first rodeo with the shade, as he created a similar set for the star back in November 2023 with a black-cherry design. And before that, the duo created a bejeweled manicure that also left us speechless. For their more-recent creation, Bachik took to Instagram to share the details behind the set with the caption, "Chocolate Cherry 4Ever." While keeping her signature coffin shape intact with Apr√©s's Gel-X Natural Coffin Medium Tips ($17), Bachik used the brand's Gel Couleur in Blood Moon ($15), followed by the Non-Wipe Glossy Top Gelcoat ($13). For a non-gel version of the polish, try the Essie Nail Polish in Berry Naughty ($10). Take a closer look at Lopez's nails below. The latest celeb to join the party? None other than Jennifer Lopez. The singer recently traded her awards-show-ready nude manicure for a fresh set of "cherry-mocha"" nails that have us simply drooling.

Lopez's latest manicure comes just as the color combo has found its way to the top of our FYPs (again), just a few months after making its viral debut last fall. Although other stars like Kate Moss and Kylie Jenner have embraced the trend, Lopez's interpretation is our favorite to date thanks to celebrity manicurist Tom Bachik. But it's far from the pair's first rodeo with the shade, as he created a similar set for the star back in November 2023 with a black-cherry design. And before that, the duo created a bejeweled manicure that also left us speechless.

For their more-recent creation, Bachik took to Instagram to share the details behind the set with the caption, "Chocolate Cherry 4Ever."
